title: THE BOB HOPE SHOW -- 1967 special : TV westerns vs. comedies
description:
With Don Adams of "Get Smart!", Steve Allen, Raymond Burr of "Ironside", Rod Cameron, Philip Carey after "Laredo" was cancelled, Jack Carter, Perry Como, Wally Cox, Bill Dana ( as Jose Jiminez ), Richard Deacon, James Drury and Doug McClure of "The Virginian", Jack Kelly, Paul Lynde, Buddy Hackett, Cameron Mitchell of 
"The High Chapparal", Ken Murray, Jack Palance, Don Rickles, Dale Robertson, 
Dan Rowan and Dick Martin, Larry Storch and Forrest Tucker post-"F Troop" ), 
Danny Thomas of "The Danny Thomas Hour", and singer Bobbie Gentry.

If this seems short at 45 minutes, it's probably because Bobbie's musical number was edited out of this copy so it could be posted on You Tube
